Enum CheckpointType

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<CheckpointType>

    public enum CheckpointType

    This enum is used to represent the checkpoint types within stages on road races.
    Version:
    2.0
    Author:
    Diogo Pacheco

    • Enum Constant Detail

      • SPRINT

        public static final CheckpointType SPRINT
        An intermediate sprint.

      • C4

        public static final CheckpointType C4
        A categorised 4 climb. The easiest categorised climbs of all, under 2km long with an average grade of around 5% or 2-3% up to 5km long.

      • C3

        public static final CheckpointType C3
        A categorised 3 climb. This could be a climb as short as 1km with a steep gradient of about 10% or a mellower climb up to 10km long with up to a 5% gradient.

      • C2

        public static final CheckpointType C2
        A categorised 2 climb. Category 2 could be a short climb, for example 5km at 8 percent, or as long as 15km at 4. percent

      • C1

        public static final CheckpointType C1
        A categorised 1 climb. Still a very significant climb, it could be a big mountain climb with a lesser gradient or a shorter climb with a steep pitch, for example 8km at 8% through to 20km at 5%.

      • HC

        public static final CheckpointType HC
        From the French term "Hors Categorie" (HC) meaning beyond categorisation. The toughest of the tough. The longest or steepest climbs, often both combined.
